    "For 30°and 50°, no vortices are present, but for 70°and 90°, a vortex appears.",
    "Due to the high Wi number with higher inlet velocities, the lip and corner vortex grow and merge into one vertex.",
    "This can be observed for the different inlet velocities from 5 mm/s (Fig. 9), 7.5 mm/s (Fig.",
    "10), and 12.5 mm/s (Fig. 11) at the 70°angle.",
    "For each inlet velocity, the vortex is the largest at the 90°angle."
